{
  "name": "Wild Cunning",
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You call out to the spirits of nature to aid you. When you cast this spell, choose one of the following effects:</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">If there are any tracks on the ground within range, you know where they are, and you make Wisdom (@skill[Survival]) checks to follow these tracks with advantage for 1 hour or until you cast this spell again.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">If there is edible forage within range, you know it and where to find it.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">If there is clean drinking water within range, you know it and where to find it.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">If there is suitable shelter for you and your companions with range, you know it and where to find.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Send the spirits to bring back wood for a fire and to set up a campsite in the area using your supplies. The spirits build the fire in a circle of stones, put up tents, unroll bedrolls, and put out any rations and water for consumption.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Have the spirits instantly break down a campsite, which includes putting out a fire, taking down tents, packing up bags, and burying any rubbish.</li></ul></div>",
      "chat": "",
      "unidentified": ""
    },
